article.description: Stefanie Stone made a free throw with eight seconds remaining to give Army a 69-68 win over Holy Cross in the championship of the Patriot League tournament.
article.headline: Army beats Holy Cross to win Patriot's NCAA berth
article.linkText: Army beats Holy Cross to win Patriot's NCAA berth
article.story:
WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Stefanie Stone made a free throw with eight seconds remaining to give Army a 69-68 win over Holy Cross in the championship of the Patriot League tournament Wednesday night.

Army (20-10) will be making its first trip to the NCAA Tournament.

Stone tipped a pass intended for Brittany Keil in the backcourt and drove to the net. She missed the layup as Keil fouled her and then missed her first free throw before making the winning shot.

Alex McGuire scored 18 points, Margaree King had 12 and Stone added 11 for Army.

Laura Aloisi had a chance to win the game for Holy Cross (16-14), but her layup caught the underside of the backboard as time expired and hundreds of camouflage-clad cadets stormed the court in celebration.

Kaitlin Foley had 17 points with 10 rebounds, and Keil scored 16 points to lead Holy Cross. The Crusaders led 67-66 with 59 seconds remaining on Jessica Conte's 10-foot baseline jumper. But McGuire hit two free throws for a 68-67 lead with 48 seconds remaining.

Foley tied it at 68, hitting the first of two free throws with 35 seconds remaining before Stone's game-winning free throw.

Army's first-year coach Maggie Dixon is the younger sister of Pittsburgh men's coach Jamie Dixon.
